  Research      Research  Research at the intersection of health, disability and rehabilitation  The UIC College of Applied Health Sciences is consistently ranked among the top 10 nationwide in research funding for colleges of allied health.  AHS researchers are awarded grants from a variety of federal and state agencies and foundations. Their research includes laboratory-based studies, community-based projects and scholarship in the humanities.      Fiscal year 2019 by the numbers    Stats and Facts     83  grants awarded to AHS faculty as primary principal investigators         $315,802  in sponsored program expenditures per tenured-track faculty (FTE)         $12,426,871  total sponsored program expenditures          Sponsored program expenditures (per fiscal year)      2019   73%  12%  15%     2018   75%  12%  12%     2017   73%  15%  13%      Federal  Private  State               Participation  Removing barriers to social participation among people with disabilities by empowering them with entrepreneurship training                       Policy  Evaluating policies and programs that impact individuals with disabilities and advocating for reform                       Balance  Helping older adults and prosthetic wearers find balance and avoid damaging falls                       Diabetes  Transforming the lives of people with diabetes by improving wound-healing                       Obesity  Collaborating across disciplines to provide better healthcare for older adults with online training                       Aging  Collaborating across disciplines to provide better healthcare for older adults with online training                       Recovery  Improving patients' ability to walk after a stroke using brain stimulation and gait training                       Autism  Creating teaching resources and learning moments for children with autism and their families                       Data simplification  Raising the bar in standards and processes for creating, using, and protecting health information to improve clinical outcomes                      What we're researching    Top research topics among AHS faculty. Select to see faculty studying a topic.       Health Promotion    Disability    Exercise Physiology    Obesity and Diabetes    Health Disparities    Cultural Competency    Aging    Biomechanics    Biomedical Informatics    Biomedical Visualization and Design    Cardiovascular Health    Children, Youth and Families    Community-Based Participatory Research    Interprofessional Education    Nutrition    Qualitative Research    Rehabilitation    Meet our faculty                 AHS Office of Research  From brainstorming ideas to preparing mountains of forms, the AHS Office of Research staff is dedicated to supporting our researchers. We let you focus on scientific development while we manage the review and submission of your proposals.   Get research support       Recent News    Taking the long view   Wednesday, April 22, 2020     Two IPL researchers are named Fellows of the American Heart Association   Tuesday, April 14, 2020     UIC explores partnership with Tecnológico de Monterrey   Wednesday, April 8, 2020     UIC opens occupational therapy clinic   Thursday, March 12, 2020     Meet the 2020 AHS Alumni Awards recipients   Monday, February 17, 2020      All AHS news     Upcoming Events     May  12   UIC Kinesiology Online ICT Information Session   Tuesday, 12:00 pm - 1:00 pm      May  13   Autism Webinar Series: The Dual Diagnosis of Down Syndrome and Autism Spectrum Disorder (DS-ASD)   Wednesday, 12:00 pm - 1:00 pm      May  15   Online DPT advising session for prospective students   Friday, 10:30 am - 12:30 pm      May  22   Virtual MS in OT Info Session   Friday, 2:00 pm - 3:00 pm      May  28   CANCELED: UIC Alumni & Recent Graduate Job Fair   Thursday      All AHS events             College of Applied Health Sciences    Back to main content           Applying    Expand Applying menu          Degrees and Deadlines